The paper focuses on object detection using deep learning, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions transfer learning, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), and unsupervised learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of thermal information suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the application of object detection in military scenarios, which may fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
